.TH "pci_enable_atomic_ops_to_root" 9 "pci_enable_atomic_ops_to_root" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_enable_atomic_ops_to_root \- enable AtomicOp requests to root port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_enable_atomic_ops_to_root
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 cap_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the PCI device
.IP "cap_mask" 12
mask of desired AtomicOp sizes, including one or more of:
PCI_EXP_DEVCAP2_ATOMIC_COMP32
PCI_EXP_DEVCAP2_ATOMIC_COMP64
PCI_EXP_DEVCAP2_ATOMIC_COMP128
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 0 if all upstream bridges support AtomicOp routing, egress
blocking is disabled on all upstream ports, and the root port supports
the requested completion capabilities (32-bit, 64-bit and/or 128-bit
AtomicOp completion), or negative otherwise.
